[DONE] utf-8 in string indexing and char: length/indexing/substr/
       string-index/split count by codepoint (not byte); chars hold a
       full codepoint and read/print/persist (savedb) as UTF-8; index
       assignment (= (s i) ch) rebuilds for variable width; als
       transpiler reads multi-byte #\X literals. utf8_* helpers in
       alcove.c. Tests: "utf8 *" block in test.alc.
[DONE] add support for documentation in function header — (def f (args)
       "docstring" body...): a leading string FOLLOWED by more body forms is
       stored (keyed by name in user_doc) and surfaced by (doc f) / (docstring
       f); a lone string body stays the return value. def-only (anonymous fn
       has no name to key by). Tests "docstring *" in test.alc.
[DONE] add support for default parameters — (def f (x (y 10)) ...): a param
       written (name default-expr) is optional; a missing arg evaluates the
       default in the frame being built, so a default can reference params
       bound earlier (def h (a (b (+ a 1))) ...). Bound in var2env; functions
       with optional params run via the AST evaluator (the bytecode fast path
       assumes exact arity, so they don't compile — correctness over speed).
       Tests "dp-*" / "default" in test.alc.
[DONE] add support for polymorphism in lambda — arity overloading via
       (defn name (PARAMS body...) (PARAMS body...) ...). Each clause is a
       param list (which may use . rest) + body; a call dispatches on the
       argument count to the matching clause (a variadic clause catches any
       count >= its fixed arity; first match wins; no match raises a catchable
       error). Implemented as a FLAG_MULTI wrapper lambda holding one ordinary
       closure per clause; invoke / vm_invoke_values intercept the flag and
       delegate to the arity-matched clause, so binding (incl. defaults /
       destructuring / rest within a clause), recursion across clauses, and
       compiled callers all reuse the existing machinery. Type-based dispatch
       was rejected — Alcove is untyped, so arity is the natural axis. Tests
       "defn *" in test.alc. (Anonymous case-lambda not added; defn is named.)
[DONE] call/cc — ESCAPE continuations (one-shot, upward). (call/cc f) calls f
       with k; (k v) makes call/cc return v, abandoning the work between. Full
       re-entrant continuations aren't feasible in a recursive C tree-walker +
       bytecode VM without a CPS/stack-copy rewrite, so this is the escape-only
       subset (like Scheme call/ec); k is valid only in call/cc's dynamic
       extent. Mechanism: (k v) yields an EXP_ERROR-tagged escape token
       (ERROR_CONT_ESCAPE, id in meta, payload in next) that propagates up the
       existing error plumbing to the matching call/cc frame. No setjmp.
       Implementing it surfaced + fixed TWO pre-existing bugs: (1) whilecmd
       swallowed body errors/escapes (re-eval'd the condition over them →
       (while true (/1 0)) would spin); (2) OP_TAIL_CALL's in-place TCO reused
       the caller's env for a CLOSURE tail-callee, resolving the closure's
       captured free vars wrong — now real (non-global) closures route through
       vm_invoke_values (top-level defs keep TCO). Tests "20g" in test.alc.
[DONE] MessagePack codec: (msgpack-encode v) -> blob, (msgpack-decode blob)
       -> value. Covers nil, t, fixnums (fixint/uint/int 8-64), floats
       (float32 decode, float64), strings/symbols (fixstr/str8-32), blobs
       (bin8-32), lists (fixarray/array16-32), string-keyed dicts
       (fixmap/map16-32); chars encode as int codepoint. Big-endian,
       bounds-checked decode. Errors (encode: unsupported type; decode:
       malformed/truncated/non-string key/trailing data) are catchable.
       Self-contained codec (alcove.c, like the savedb serializer); tests
       "20i" in test.alc.
